This paper deals with resource allocation in wireless small cell networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of game theory to model the behavior of small cell base stations (SCBSs) suggests that the paper may also belong to the game theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of context information to optimize resource allocation, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, and cs.MM, in that order.
